# Phase 7.4 / D-01 — Hexaly platform license template.
#
# This file is intentionally checked in as a TEMPLATE only. The real .lic
# from Hexaly contains binary data + a human-readable EXPIRES= line. The
# adapter (app/domains/solver/adapters/hexaly.py) reads the file at startup
# and parses the EXPIRES line via regex (_license_utils._extract_expires_at).
#
# Operator workflow:
#   1. Receive the real .lic from Hexaly (commercial channel — out of band).
#   2. SSH to the production host:
#        ssh jaot@<server> sudo install -m 0600 -o root -g root /tmp/hexaly.lic /etc/jaot/hexaly.lic
#   3. Run `bash deploy/deploy.sh standard-rotate` from your dev workstation.
#
# Local dev: place a Hexaly trial .lic at deploy/secrets/hexaly.lic
# (or whatever path docker-compose.yml maps in dev). The .gitignore entry
# below ensures the real file never lands in git.
#
# Format hint (Hexaly may change this — when in doubt, contact support):
EXPIRES=2099-12-31
HEXALY_LICENSE_BLOB=<binary>...<more binary>...
